{"title_page": "2013 New Orleans Saints season", "text_new": "{{Infobox NFL season\n| logo =\n| team = New Orleans Saints\n| year = 2013\n| record = 11\u20135\n| division_place = 2nd [[NFC South]]\n| coach = [[Sean Payton]]\n| owner = [[Tom Benson]]\n| general_manager = [[Mickey Loomis]]\n| stadium = [[Mercedes-Benz Superdome]]\n| playoffs = '''Won''' [[2013\u201314 NFL playoffs|Wild Card Playoffs]] (at [[2013 Philadelphia Eagles season|Eagles]]) 26\u201324<br>Lost [[2013\u201314 NFL playoffs|Divisional Playoffs]] (at [[2013 Seattle Seahawks season|Seahawks]]) 15\u201323\n| pro bowlers = [[Drew Brees]] (QB)<br>[[Jahri Evans]] (G)<br>[[Jimmy Graham]] (TE)<br>[[Cameron Jordan]] (DE)\n| AP All-pros = [[Jimmy Graham]] ''(1st team)''<br>[[Jahri Evans]] ''(2nd team)''\n|uniform = File:Saints uniforms12.png\n|colors = Black, Old gold, White\n{{color box|black}} {{color box|#d2b887}} {{color box|#FFFFFF}}\n| shortnavlink   = Saints seasons\n}}\nThe '''2013 New Orleans Saints season''' was the franchise's 47th season in the [[National Football League]] and the 38th to host games at the [[Mercedes-Benz Superdome]]. It also marked the seventh season under [[List of New Orleans Saints head coaches|head coach]] [[Sean Payton]], who returned to the team after serving a one-year suspension for his involvement in the team's [[New Orleans Saints bounty scandal|2012 bounty scandal]].\n\nThe Saints improved their 7\u20139 record from last season, going 11\u20135 and making the [[2013\u201314 NFL playoffs|playoffs]] as the sixth seed. They earned the franchise's first-ever road postseason victory, with a 26\u201324 win over the [[2013 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia Eagles]] in the Wild Card round, ending the drought at 0\u20135. However, the Saints were eliminated by the eventual Super Bowl champion [[2013 Seattle Seahawks season|Seattle Seahawks]] in the divisional round, by a score of 23\u201315. The 2013 season was also the second time in three years the Saints went 8\u20130 at home.\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Offseason==\n===Signings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! Pos. !! Player !! 2012 Team !! Contract\n|-\n| CB || [[Keenan Lewis]] || [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] || 5 years, $25.5 million\n|-\n| TE || [[Benjamin Watson]] || [[Cleveland Browns]] || 3 years, $4.9 million\n|-\n| LB || [[Victor Butler]] || [[Dallas Cowboys]] || 2 years, $3 million\n|-\n| DE || [[Kenyon Coleman]] || [[Dallas Cowboys]] || 1 year, $1 million\n|-\n| CB || [[Chris Carr (American football)|Chris Carr]] || [[San Diego Chargers]] || 1 year, $840,000\n|-\n| QB || [[Luke McCown]] || [[Atlanta Falcons]] || 1 year, $840,000\n|-\n| OT || [[Jason Smith (American football)|Jason Smith]] || [[New York Jets]] || 1 year, $780,000\n|-\n| WR || [[Robert Meachem]] || [[San Diego Chargers]] || 1 year, $715,000\n|-\n|}\n\n===Re-Signings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! Pos. !! Player !! Contract\n|-\n| WR || [[Courtney Roby]] || 1 year, $905,000\n|-\n| LB || [[Will Herring]] || 1 year, $765,000\n|-\n| OLB || [[Ramon Humber]] || 1 year, $740,000\n|-\n|}\n\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! Pos. !! Player !! 2013 Team \n|-\n| OT ||[[Jermon Bushrod]] || [[Chicago Bears]]\n|-\n| QB ||[[Chase Daniel]] || [[Kansas City Chiefs]]\n|-\n| LB ||[[Jonathan Casillas]] || [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]\n|-\n| S ||[[Jim Leonhard]] || [[Buffalo Bills]]\n|-\n| CB ||[[Elbert Mack]] || [[Houston Texans]]\n|-\n| QB ||[[Seneca Wallace]] || [[San Francisco 49ers]]\n|-\n| WR ||[[Steve Breaston]] || \n|-\n| LB || [[Scott Shanle]] || \n|-\n|}\n\n==2013 draft class==\n{{main|2013 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n! [[List of New Orleans Saints first-round draft picks|1]] || 15\n| [[Kenny Vaccaro]] || [[Safety (American and Canadian football position)|Safety]] || [[Texas Longhorns football|Texas]]\n|-\n! rowspan=2|3 || 75\n| [[Terron Armstead]] || [[Tackle (American and Canadian football)|Offensive tackle]] || [[Arkansas\u2013Pine Bluff Golden Lions football|Arkansas\u2013Pine Bluff]]\n|-\n!  82\n| [[John Jenkins (defensive tackle)|John Jenkins]] || [[Defensive tackle]] || [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]]\n|-\n! 5 || 144\n| [[Kenny Stills]] || [[Wide receiver]] || [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]]\n|-\n! 6 || 183\n| [[Rufus Johnson (American football)|Rufus Johnson]] || [[Defensive end]] || [[Tarleton State Texans football|Tarleton State]]\n|}\n'''Notes'''\nThe Saints did not have selections in the second, fourth, or seventh rounds. They forfeited their second-round selection as part of the punishment for the team's [[New Orleans Saints bounty scandal|2012 bounty scandal]]. They acquired the No. 82 selection in a trade that sent two fourth-round selections, Nos. 106 and 109 overall, to the [[Miami Dolphins]]. The No. 106 selection had been acquired in a trade that sent [[running back]] [[Chris Ivory]] to the [[New York Jets]]. The Saints traded their seventh-round selection to the [[Seattle Seahawks]] in exchange for [[linebacker]] [[Barrett Ruud]].\n\n==Staff==\n{{NFL final staff\n|Year=2013\n|TeamName=New Orleans Saints\n|BC1=black\n|FC1=white\n|BDC1=#9F8958\n|Front Office=\n*Owner/Chairman \u2013 [[Tom Benson]]\n*Owner/Vice Chairman \u2013 [[Rita Benson LeBlanc]]\n*President \u2013 [[Dennis Lauscha]]\n*Executive Vice President/General Manager \u2013 [[Mickey Loomis]]\n*Director of Football Administration \u2013 [[Khai Harley]]\n*Director of Pro Scouting \u2013 [[Ryan Pace]]\n*Director of College Scouting \u2013 [[Rick Reiprish]]\n*Assistant Director of College Scouting \u2013 [[Brian Adams (American football)|Brian Adams]]\n|Head Coaches=\n*Head Coach \u2013 [[Sean Payton]]\n*Assistant Head Coach/Linebackers \u2013 [[Joe Vitt]]\n|Offensive Coaches=\n*Offensive Coordinator \u2013 [[Pete Carmichael, Jr.]]\n*Quarterbacks \u2013 [[J